Description 
This is a generalizability attempt on the claim 4 claim: 
 
In Experiment 1, an ANOVA on participants’ rate of utilitarian responses across four scenarios, 
with mortality salience (death vs. pain) as a between-subjects factor and scenario version 
(harm-conflict and harm-control) as a within-subjects factor yielded a significant interaction 
effect, F(1, 83) = 6.89; p = .01; partial eta squared = 0.08. 
 
from Trémolière et al (2012). 
 
The statistical evidence is: F(1, 83) = 6.89; p = .01; partial eta squared = 0.08. 
